[[Gn 14,18]]In those days, Melchizedek, king of Salem, brought out bread and wine, and being a priest of God Most High, he blessed Abram with these words:
[[Gn 14,19]]Blessed be Abram by God Most High, the creator of heaven and earth;
[[Gn 14,20]]And blessed be God Most High, who delivered your foes into your hand." Then Abram gave him a tenth of everything.
